Get token info
The
```
getTokenInfo(tokenId: string): Promise<TokenInfoRow | undefined>
```
methods finds basic information about a Circles token. This includes the creation timestamp, circles version, token type (human or group) and the address of the avatar that created the token.
Copy
```
const tokenInfo = await data.getTokenInfo("0x...");
if (tokenInfo) {
console.log("Token is a Circles token");
} else {
console.log("Token is not a Circles token");
```
