Get trust relations
The
```
getTrustRelations(avatar: string, pageSize: number): CirclesQuery<TrustListRow>
```
method can be used to query the effective trust events for an avatar. Already expired or removed trust relations are omitted from the results.
Copy
```
const trustsQuery = data.getTrustRelations("0x...", 25);
console.log("No trust events yet");
return;
```
The results of this method contain one row per incoming or outgoing event. This is useful when you need to know when a relation was established. However, if you just want to display a contact list you should consider using
```
getAggregatedTrustRelations(avatarAddress: string): Promise<TrustRelationRow[]>
```
instead.
